peptide that needs to occur for viral entry. The S1 subunit contains a receptor-binding domain (RBD) encompassing the receptor-binding motif (RBM) that binds ACE2. The S2 contains a fusion peptide (FP), that penetrates into cell membranes and mediates fusion between the viral and host membranes to release viral proteins and genome.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:25:04 +0000 2026"}